<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4245] When a core is registering with ZooKeeper, the timeout to find the leader in the cluster state is 30 seconds rather than leaderVoteWait + extra time.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4245</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The sub calls to get the leader had a 30 second wait which effectively short circuits the top level timeout with regards to waiting for an initial leader. Not a big deal in smaller clusters, but can end up as problem with larger clusters where a node might timeout and need to be restarted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
